data.description: This home just makes my jaw drop in awe when I pass by and see this gorgeous city home. The contours and angles of this home really showcases the brick exterior. Walking through the front entrance, it opens up into a large living room with hardwood floors and a wood burning fireplace. The den/bonus room to the right is currently used as a 1st floor bedroom, but your imagination can make this bonus your desirable area. The kitchen opens up into the 2nd living room with high ceilings. The kitchen has a large industrial gas stove and plenty of cabinets that were freshly painted. The additional living room leads out to a grand deck overlooking the ginormous back yard. The guest bathroom with a stand-up shower is on the 1st floor.  Upstairs, there's new carpet throughout. 3 great sized bedrooms and another full bath. One of the bedrooms has a bonus walkup entrance into the attic that could be made into additional space for play or a hang out. The basement houses the laundry area and a partially finished area. The driveway offers plenty of parking near the 2-stall detached garage. This home is close to the hospital, schools, amenities and Ft. Drum. Take a look, you may just fall in love!
